</m:msub>
<m:mo> + </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> ω </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub></m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math></para>
<para id="element-48">When disks come in contact and rotate about a common axis with equal angular velocity, they acquire common angular velocity, say ”ω”. Since, 
two disks are rotating about a common axis of rotation, the MI of the combination is arithmetic sum of individual MIs. The moment of inertia of the composite system, “
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> C </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
” is given as :
</para>
<para id="element-49">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> C </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> + </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-50">Thus, final angular momentum of the system is :
</para>
<para id="element-51">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> L </m:mi>
<m:mn> f </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mo> ( </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> + </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> I </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> ) </m:mo> 
<m:mi> ω </m:mi>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-52">
Putting values in the equation of conservation of angular momentum, we have :
</para>
<para id="element-53">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mo> ⇒ </m:mo> 
